column26: Organ donation typically involves the donation of deceased organs, as living organs cannot be donated.
column27: Brain death is a state in which the patient's brain functions have permanently ceased, resulting in the inability to breathe or sustain a heartbeat.
column28: Living organs can usually be donated only to close relatives, such as immediate family members.
column29: Any doctor can determine brain death.
column30: In case of Brain Death, Organ removal must be performed only after brain death is determined.
column31: People with any disease can donate organs.
column32: People of any age can donate organs.
column33: If citizens haven't expressed their approval for organ donation during their lifetime, their spouses, adult children, and parents can jointly express consent after their death.
